<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="112" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1166,1767]" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1634,1659]" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species is fairly similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Ude, 1924" authorityName="Ude" authorityYear="1924" box="[692,1111,1634,1659]" class="Clitellata" family="Megascolecidae" genus="Polypheretima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opisthopora" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="sepikensis">
<emphasis box="[692,979,1635,1659]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Polypheretima sepikensis</emphasis>
Ude, 
<number box="[1055,1111,1635,1659]" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" value="1924.0">1924</number>
</taxonomicName>
, but it is metandric, genital markings and accessory glands are absent, and the first dorsal pore is in 
<number box="[939,964,1671,1695]" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" value="11.0">11</number>
/ 
<number box="[974,1001,1671,1695]" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" value="12.0">12</number>
. There are crescentic markings in front of and behind the male pores, but they differ from the crescentic genital markings of 
<taxonomicName authority="Easton (1979)" authorityName="Easton" authorityYear="1979" box="[1023,1432,1707,1731]" class="Clitellata" family="Megascolecidae" genus="Metapheretima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opisthopora" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1023,1193,1707,1731]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Metapheretima</emphasis>
sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Easton" box="[1270,1432,1707,1731]" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" refString="Easton, E. G. (1979) A revision of the ' acaecate' earthworms of the Pheretima group (Megascolecidae: Oligochaeta): Archipheretima, Metapheretima, Planapheretima, Pleionogaster and Polypheretima. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Zoology, 35, 1 - 126." type="journal article" year="1979">
Easton (
<number box="[1363,1424,1707,1731]" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" value="1979.0">1979</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<typeStatus box="[151,218,1743,1767]" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Types</typeStatus>
were rechecked for this study.
</paragraph>
